14th Avenue, north side, at 143rd Street, showing a colonial mansion, owned by A. J. Provost in 1873 and by J. R. Egan in 1891. The mansion is on a hill and overlooks Long Island Sound. The mansion stands in the direct path of the proposed 143rd Street.

P. L. Sperr

March 3, 1932

14th Avenue, north side, at 143rd Street. Shown is the white colonial mansion at the above location which was owned by A.J. Provost in 1873 and by J.P. Egan in 1891. The view is south from near 10th Avenue, across the Long Island Railroad station. View 2 shows the barn, with weathercock on top, on the estate.

P. L. Sperr
